This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing (NLP) and the identification of hypernymy relations. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it discusses the use of supervised and unsupervised methods for hypernymy detection. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves the analysis of different distributional semantic models for hypernymy identification. Finally, it could be classified under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as it discusses the performance and reliability of different methods for hypernymy detection.
